46:23.914 --> 46:29.262
Those are my six arguments for why you cannot treat the enjoyment of Jesus as something.

46:29.322 --> 46:34.329
Peripheral, marginal, non-essential is very essential.

46:34.750 --> 46:37.554
God, you made known to me the path of life

46:37.634 --> 46:44.043
in your presence is fullness of joy at your right hand are pleasures forever more.

46:44.143 --> 46:51.073
And I would just look out upon you even though it's dark and I can't see faces real clearly, you can see mine, it's real big over there probably.

46:51.794 --> 47:06.674
And I just wanna close by saying, if that's not the way you experience Jesus or the way you experience God, as the fullness of joy, the forever

47:06.850 --> 47:10.855
Joy, that verse from Psalm 16 is an invitation to you.

47:12.036 --> 47:15.380
I call it an obligation, but it's such a happy obligation.

47:15.921 --> 47:19.505
And God is saying to you tonight, my arms are wide to you.

47:19.525 --> 47:21.507
I love being enjoyed.

47:21.547 --> 47:26.774
That's the way I get glory is if people enjoy me.

47:27.114 --> 47:30.418
So I'm inviting you, come and join me.

47:30.458 --> 47:30.999
It's free.

47:31.079 --> 47:33.842
My son covered all your sins.

47:34.210 --> 47:37.016
My son provided a way into my favor.

47:37.336 --> 47:39.821
I'll adopt you into my family.

47:40.743 --> 47:42.286
You will live with me forever.

47:42.647 --> 47:45.092
You will be as happy as you can possibly be.

47:45.152 --> 47:48.459
You will never be bored forever and ever.

47:48.639 --> 47:51.445
That's why I have given you my book.

47:51.465 --> 47:54.130
That's why I sent John Piper down to Midlothian.

